sec.p:
TESC corresponds to a new paradigm of near-field optical microscopy. While previous near-field optical microscopy efforts have generally focused on a minimally invasive tip-sample interaction to obtain an unperturbed spectroscopic signature (
  
   24
  ), TESC moves from a traditionally nonperturbative to a strongly perturbative regime in which the tip acts as a nanocavity to induce, probe, and control quantum hybrid states for all-optical room temperature quantum metrology and sensing at the nanoscale.
